`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- FPS camera rotation order `"YXZ"` is critical: it applies yaw (Y) first, then pitch (X), which matches the physical intuition of "turn left/right, then look up/down" — wrong order causes gimbal lock artifacts
- `useThree().camera` from R3F returns the same object as the `<PerspectiveCamera makeDefault>` ref since `makeDefault` registers it as the R3F scene camera — no need for two separate refs
- Pointer lock goes on `canvas.addEventListener("click")` — NOT `document` — so the user must click the 3D canvas specifically to enter look mode
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
